[[File:Labslogo thumb text.png]]
A place where magic happen
== About == This is Wikimedia Labs. It is meant to make it easier for developers and system administrators to try out improvements to Wikimedia infrastructure, including MediaWiki, and to do analytics and bot work. [[Help:Terminology|Labs Account Holders]] are governed by the [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Wikimedia_Labs/Terms_of_use Labs terms of service]. The [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Wikimedia_Labs/Agreement_to_disclosure_of_personally_identifiable_information agreement to disclosure of personally identifiable information] covers [[Help:Terminology|Labs End-Users]].

This is the "Shell Access Request" template. It should be called in the following format: 
{{Shell Access Request
|User Name=
|Justification=
|Completed=
|Comments=
}}
The Comments parameter is optional, and should only be used by admins processing the request. Edit the page to see the template text. ; User Name: : {{{User Name|}}} ; Justification for shell access: : [[Shell Justification::{{{Justification|}}}]] ; Has this request been completed by an admin?: : [[Is Completed::{{{Completed|}}}]] {{#if:{{{Comments|}}} |;Additional comments: : {{{Comments|}}}|}} [[Category:Shell Access Requests]]

revision.text: Warning: This is a labs instance and is not the production labsconsole. Please do not use real credentials here. This wiki has been loaded with subsets of production LDAP information, and as such has user accounts used in production, but they can not be used for authentication. You should create a new account here prefixed with: "TEST"; for instance: "TEST Ryan Lane" for username and "testlaner" for shell account name.
